The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 09 August is 268,312 (476.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 August, there were 5,059 new confirmed cases (9.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 July, there were 4,999 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (60 extra cases).
